-- ECM Real Estate Bondholders Vote to Approve Additional Restructuring Talks
-- B y   D o u g l a s   L y t l e
-- 2010-11-05T07:06:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-05/ecm-real-estate-bondholders-vote-to-approve-additional-restructuring-talks.html
Bondholders of ECM Real Estate
Invesments AG voted at a Nov. 4 meeting to continue talks on
restructuring their holdings, the company said in a regulatory
news filing today.  The motion to continue talks was passed with 12,203 votes,
or 82.63 percent. A total of 2,565 votes, or 17.37 percent,
abstained, the statement said.  “The meeting resolves that further negotiations need to
take place among the stakeholders involved in the restructuring
process,” the statement said. “At the moment it is not
possible to vote about changes to the terms and conditions.”  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Douglas Lytle at 
 dlytle@bloomberg.net  